---Sprite source data.
---Please note that in gameplay we should operate over SpriteData (assets), not Object Sprites (data containers)!
---Creating multiple ObjectSprites for the same texture region leads to adding a copy into Subsystem and Texture Atlas.
---@class FObjectSprite
---@field protected Id FObjectSpriteId @Should be automatically generated by parent's SpriteData in Unreal Editor or runtime in-game Sprite Editor
---@field protected SourceTexture TSoftObjectPtr<UTexture2D>
---@field protected StartUV FVector2D @Source Textures region UV0. Changing this after the sprite has been added to Static Sprite Subsystem makes no effect.
---@field protected SizeUV FVector2D @Source Textures region UV1. Changing this after the sprite has been added to Static Sprite Subsystem makes no effect.
---@field protected bShouldUseCanvasRenderTarget boolean @Whether to add the sprite into Runtime Texture Atlas instead of drawing the SourceTexture. Joining multiple sprites into single Atlas leads to massive Draw Call reduction, but has pixel size limitations.
---@field protected MaterialOverride UMaterialInterface @Only use if you need non-default material for the sprite. Avoid overriding materials, since we cannot merge multiple shaders in single draw call. Leave nullptr to use the default material. Material needs to have 'SpriteTexture' texture parameter to receive the sprite. Changing this after sprite has been added to Static Sprite Subsystem makes no effect.
---@field protected PivotPoint FVector2D @Mesh offset from texture center. Stored in _TPX (original texture pixels, TQ-agnostic). Convert to UU: PivotPoint * FStaticSpriteSettings::OriginalTextureSizeToUuRatio.
---@field protected TextureRegionSizePx FIntVector2 @Size of the sprite (texture region) in _TPX — original texture pixels, TQ-agnostic. Auto-generated and cached to prevent referencing the SourceTexture. Use GetTextureRegionSizePx_TPX() / GetTextureRegionSizePx_SPX() for typed access.
---@field protected RenderBoundsExtent FVector2D @Box Extent for RenderBounds, measured for SourceTexture region dimensions. Stored in _TPX (original texture size space, no TextureQuality applied). Convert to UU: RenderBoundsExtent * FStaticSpriteSettings::OriginalTextureSizeToUuRatio. Use GetRenderBoundsExtent_TPX() for typed access.
---@field protected Sockets TMap<string, FSpriteSocket>
---@field protected Tile_ConditionalNeighborMask integer @For Tile set sprite elements only. Defines a mask (From North, clockwise) of neighbor cells that need to have a specific condition (free or occupied). 1 = conditional neighbor, see the value in Tile_NeighborConditions; 0 = we don't care, can be any.
---@field protected Tile_NeighborConditions integer @For Tile set sprite elements only. Defines a mask (From North, clockwise) of neighbor cells that need to have a specific tile condition (free or occupied). 1 = needs to be occupied, 0 = not [it either needs to be free; OR we don't care for it at all, if its bit == 0 in Tile_ConditionalNeighborMask]).
---@field protected bTileSetMaskEditCondition_EditorOnly boolean @Inherited from parent SpriteData to set edit condition for TileSetMask field.
FObjectSprite = {}
